: "2,350 SF"}, "feature_key": "gla", "diff_comps": ["C1", "C3"], "diff_directions": {"C1": "superior", "C3": "inferior"}}, {"label": "Bathrooms", "subject": "3 full", "comp_values": {"C1": "3 full", "C2": "3 full", "C3": "3 full"}, "diff_comps": []}, {"label": "Garage", "subject": "2-car", "comp_values": {"C1": "2-car", "C2": "2-car", "C3": "2-car"}, "diff_comps": []}, {"label": "Year Built", "subject": "2009", "comp_values": {"C1": "2009", "C2": "2008", "C3": "2010"}, "diff_comps": []}, {"label": "Condition", "subject": "Good", "comp_values": {"C1": "Good", "C2": "Average", "C3": "Good"}, "feature_key": "cnd", "diff_comps": ["C2"], "diff_directions": {"C2": "inferior"}}, {"label": "Location", "subject": "Standard", "comp_values": {"C1": "Amenitied/Gated", "C2": "Similar", "C3": "Amenitied/Gated"}, "feature_key": "loc", "diff_comps": ["C1", "C3"], "diff_directions": {"C1": "superior", "C3": "superior"}}], "step2": {"tabs": [{"key": "paired", "label": "Paired Sales Analysis", "intro": "Use the supporting market data to derive contributory values for each adjustment type. Four tables — one per adjustment type. Note that GLA Pair 4 diverges from Pairs 1–3 and must be addressed in your reconciliation. Three of the four adjustment types have no cost method, so paired sales is the primary support tool.", "tables": [{"kind": "paired_dollar_per_unit", "feature_key": "gla", "title": "GLA Pairs — Calculate $/SF", "instruction": "Each pair is confirmed equivalent except for GLA. Divide Price Difference ÷ SF Difference. Pair 4 is a notable outlier — bracket toward Pairs 1–3 and address Pair 4 explicitly in your reconciliation rationale.", "input_label": "Your $/SF", "input_suffix": "/SF", "rows": [{"label": "1", "cells": ["2,300 SF / $358,000", "2,450 SF / $365,200", "150 SF", "$7,200"]}, {"label": "2", "cells": ["2,350 SF / $362,000", "2,500 SF / $369,500", "150 SF", "$7,500"]}, {"label": "3", "cells": ["2,400 SF / $370,000", "2,550 SF / $377,700", "150 SF", "$7,700"]}, {"label": "4", "cells": ["2,250 SF / $345,000", "2,450 SF / $356,700", "200 SF", "$11,700"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "Sale A (SF / Price)", "Sale B (SF / Price)", "SF Diff", "Price Diff"], "concluded_label": "Concluded GLA Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Weight Pairs 1–3; address Pair 4''s divergence."}, {"kind": "paired_dollar_diff", "feature_key": "loc", "title": "Location Pairs — Standard vs. Amenitied/Gated", "instruction": "No cost method is available for location adjustments. Calculate the price difference (Amenitied/Gated minus Standard) for each pair. Note Pair 4 diverges from Pairs 1–3.", "input_label": "Your Price Difference", "input_suffix": "", "rows": [{"label": "1", "cells": ["$358,000", "$373,000"]}, {"label": "2", "cells": ["$365,000", "$379,500"]}, {"label": "3", "cells": ["$371,000", "$386,500"]}, {"label": "4", "cells": ["$355,000", "$372,000"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "Standard Sale", "Amenitied/Gated Sale"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Location Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Pairs 1–3 cluster tightly; address Pair 4."}, {"kind": "paired_dollar_diff", "feature_key": "cnd", "title": "Condition Pairs — Good vs. Average", "instruction": "No cost method is available for condition. Calculate the price difference (Good minus Average) for each pair.", "input_label": "Your Price Difference", "input_suffix": "", "rows": [{"label": "1", "cells": ["$350,000", "$362,500"]}, {"label": "2", "cells": ["$345,000", "$357,000"]}, {"label": "3", "cells": ["$355,000", "$367,800"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "Average Sale", "Good Sale"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Condition Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Pairs cluster tightly — strong market support."}, {"kind": "paired_pct_per_month", "feature_key": "date", "title": "Market Conditions — Resale Pair Analysis", "instruction": "The same properties sold twice. For each pair, calculate the monthly appreciation rate using: (Resale − Original) ÷ Original ÷ Months × 100", "input_label": "Your %/Month", "input_suffix": "%/mo", "rows": [{"label": "A", "cells": ["$354,000", "$365,900", "11"]}, {"label": "B", "cells": ["$361,000", "$373,100", "12"]}, {"label": "C", "cells": ["$348,000", "$360,460", "10"]}], "column_headers": ["Property", "Original Sale Price", "Resale Price", "Months"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Monthly Rate", "concluded_helper": "Average or bracket your three results."}]}, {"key": "cost", "label": "Cost-Based Support", "intro": "Calculate the depreciated contributory value for GLA only. No cost method is applicable for location, condition, or market conditions adjustments — paired sales is the sole support tool for those three.", "items": [{"kind": "cost_calc", "feature_key": "gla", "title": "GLA Contributory Value ($/SF)", "fact_rows": [["RCN", "$82.00 / SF"], ["Effective Age", "15 years"], ["Economic Life", "60 years"], ["Depreciation Rate", "15 ÷ 60 = 25%"], ["Formula", "$82.00 × (1 − 0.25) = ?"]], "input_suffix": "/SF"}]}], "reconciliation": {"instruction": "Review both method indications and enter your reconciled adjustment for each item. Cost is available for GLA only — for location, condition, and market conditions, your paired sales conclusion is the sole support.", "items": [{"feature_key": "gla", "label": "GLA Adjustment ($/SF)"}, {"feature_key": "loc", "label": "Location Adjustment ($)"}, {"feature_key": "cnd", "label": "Condition Adjustment ($)"}, {"feature_key": "date", "label": "Market Conditions Adjustment (%/mo)"}]}}, "step3": {"instruction": "Apply your reconciled adjustments to each comparable. Use a NEGATIVE value where the comp is superior to the subject, and a POSITIVE value where it is inferior. For Comp 2 (market conditions), calculate the dollar amount as: $350,000 × 11 months × your reconciled %/mo ÷ 100. Comp 3 has opposing adjustments — GLA positive (smaller, inferior) but Location negative (gated, superior); apply each independently.", "applicable": {"C1": ["gla", "loc"], "C2": ["cnd", "date"], "C3": ["gla", "loc"]}, "method_dropdown": ["Paired Sales Analysis", "Location Paired Sales Analysis", "Market Conditions (Resale Pairs)", "Cost-Based Support", "Grouped Paired Sales", "Regression Analysis", "Appraiser Judgment / Extraction"], "support_min_chars": 15}, "step4": {"show_net_gross_panel": false}}'::jsonb,
  '{"step1_correct_flags": {"C1": ["gla", "loc"], "C2": ["cnd", "date"], "C3": ["gla", "loc"]}, "step1_rationale": "Comp 1 is 150 SF larger (superior GLA) and in an amenitied/gated community (superior location) — two adjustments. Comp 2 is in average condition (inferior to subject''s good) and sold 11 months ago in an appreciating market — two adjustments. Comp 3 is 100 SF smaller (inferior GLA) but in an amenitied/gated community (superior location) — two adjustments with opposing directions. All other features (bathrooms, garage, year built) are equivalent across all three comparables.", "step2_tables": {"paired": {"gla": {"pair_answers": [48.0, 50.0, 51.33, 58.5], "concluded_range": [48.0, 52.0], "rationale": "Pairs 1–3 cluster tightly at $48.00–$51.33/SF — a defensible, narrow market indication. Pair 4 diverges to $58.50/SF and should be excluded with documented reasoning (different submarket, anomalous sale, or data recording error). Bracket conclusion in the $48–$52/SF range based on Pairs 1–3."}, "loc": {"pair_answers": [15000, 14500, 15500, 17000], "concluded_range": [14500, 16000], "rationale": "Pairs 1–3 produce $14,500–$15,500 — a tight bracket. Pair 4''s $17,000 result is an outlier and should be addressed but not weighted heavily. Reconcile within $14,500–$16,000."}, "cnd": {"pair_answers": [12500, 12000, 12800], "concluded_range": [12000, 12800], "rationale": "Three pairs produce $12,000–$12,800 — tight market support for the Good vs. Average condition increment."}, "date": {"pair_answers": [0.306, 0.28, 0.358], "concluded_range": [0.3, 0.34], "rationale": "Three resale pairs produce 0.28%, 0.31%, and 0.36%/mo. The midpoint range of approximately 0.30–0.34%/mo represents typical appreciation over the relevant period."}}, "cost": {"gla": {"answer": 61.5, "rationale": "$82.00 × (1 − 0.25) = $61.50/SF. Cost sits well above paired sales evidence ($48–$52/SF) — a credible ceiling. Weight paired sales."}}}, "step2_reconciliation": {"gla": {"range": [48.0, 52.0], "rationale": "Paired sales support a tight $48–$52/SF range based on Pairs 1–3. Pair 4 ($58.50/SF) is excluded with documented reasoning. Cost support of $61.50/SF is a credible ceiling. Reconcile in the $50/SF range, weighting paired sales heavily."}, "loc": {"range": [14500, 16000], "rationale": "Paired sales support $14,500–$16,000 from Pairs 1–3, with Pair 4 ($17,000) noted but not weighted. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near the midpoint."}, "cnd": {"range": [12000, 12800], "rationale": "Three pairs produce a tight $12,000–$12,800 bracket. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near the midpoint."}, "date": {"range": [0.3, 0.34], "rationale": "Paired sales support 0.30–0.34%/mo. No cost method applicable for market conditions. Reconcile near the midpoint at approximately 0.32%/mo."}}, "step3_adjustments": {"C1": {"gla": {"direction": "negative", "amount_per_unit": -50.0, "units": 150, "computed_amount": -7500, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 1 is 150 SF larger than the subject (superior). At a reconciled rate of $50/SF (drawn from Pairs 1–3), the GLA adjustment is −$7,500. Round to nearest $50."}, "loc": {"direction": "negative", "amount": -15250, "method": "Location Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 1 is in an amenitied/gated community (superior to the subject''s standard location). The location premium derived from Pairs 1–3 is approximately $15,250 (midpoint of the $14,500–$16,000 range)."}}, "C2": {"cnd": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 12400, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 2 is in average condition versus the subject''s good condition (inferior). The condition increment from three paired sales is approximately $12,400 (midpoint of $12,000–$12,800)."}, "date": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 12320, "method": "Market Conditions (Resale Pairs)", "rationale": "Comp 2 sold 11 months ago in an appreciating market (inferior date). At a reconciled rate of 0.32%/mo: $350,000 × 11 × 0.32 ÷ 100 = $12,320. Round to nearest $50."}}, "C3": {"gla": {"direction": "positive", "amount_per_unit": 50.0, "units": 100, "computed_amount": 5000, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 3 is 100 SF smaller than the subject (inferior). At a reconciled rate of $50/SF, the GLA adjustment is +$5,000."}, "loc": {"direction": "negative", "amount": -15250, "method": "Location Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 3 is in an amenitied/gated community (superior). Same location premium as applied to Comp 1: approximately $15,250 negative. Comp 3 has opposing GLA and Location adjustments — both must be applied independently."}}}, "step4_adjusted_prices": {"C1": {"unadjusted": 398000, "adjusted": 375250}, "C2": {"unadjusted": 350000, "adjusted": 374720}, "C3": {"unadjusted": 380000, "adjusted": 369750}}, "step4_reconciliation_narrative": "Adjusted prices cluster in a tight band of approximately $369,750–$375,250 — a spread of roughly $5,500. The $372,000 contract price falls comfortably within this bracket. Despite four different adjustment types applied across three comparables (six total adjustments), the market evidence converges. Comp 3''s opposing GLA-positive / Location-negative adjustments demonstrate that net and gross adjustments tell different stories — the modest net adjustment masks two real market-driven movements that should be discussed in the report. The advanced-level teaching points are: (1) the GLA Pair 4 outlier requires explicit exclusion rather than averaging, (2) three of four adjustment types lack cost support and rely entirely on paired sales evidence, and (3) Comp 3''s opposing-direction adjustments require gross adjustment commentary. Despite these complexities, the value indication strongly supports the contract price.", "tolerance_note": "Student answers are accepted within ±5% of model derived values for paired-sales calculations and within the indicated reconciliation range. Step 3 adjustments accepted within ±13% of the computed amount for GLA, ±12% for location and condition, and ±16% for market conditions (which compounds rounding across rate × months × price)."}'::jsonb
FROM scenarios s
JOIN scenario_categories sc ON sc.id = s.category_id
JOIN module_sections ms ON ms.id = sc.section_id
JOIN section_fields f ON f.section_id = ms.id AND f.field_key = 'adjustment_grid'
WHERE sc.code = 'M2-S4-C1'
  AND s.order_index = 3;

