"label": "2", "cells": ["$260,000", "$266,500"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "2 Full Bath Sale", "2.5 Bath Sale"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Bathroom Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Bracket your two results."}]}, {"key": "cost", "label": "Cost-Based Support", "intro": "Calculate the depreciated contributory value for both adjustment types. In litigation, cost support provides a useful cross-check that strengthens credibility under cross-examination.", "items": [{"kind": "cost_calc", "feature_key": "gla", "title": "GLA Contributory Value ($/SF)", "fact_rows": [["RCN", "$78.00 / SF"], ["Effective Age", "23 years"], ["Economic Life", "60 years"], ["Depreciation Rate", "23 ÷ 60 = 38.3%"], ["Formula", "$78.00 × (1 − 0.383) = ?"]], "input_suffix": "/SF"}, {"kind": "cost_calc", "feature_key": "bath", "title": "Bathroom Cost (Half-Bath Addition)", "fact_rows": [["Cost to Add Half Bath", "$11,000"], ["Effective Age", "23 years"], ["Economic Life", "60 years"], ["Depreciation Rate", "38.3%"], ["Formula", "$11,000 × (1 − 0.383) = ?"]], "input_suffix": ""}]}], "reconciliation": {"instruction": "Review both method indications and enter your reconciled adjustment for each item. For GLA, paired sales and cost converge — strong support. For bathrooms, cost typically functions as a ceiling above paired sales evidence.", "items": [{"feature_key": "gla", "label": "GLA Adjustment ($/SF)"}, {"feature_key": "bath", "label": "Bathroom Adjustment ($)"}]}}, "step3": {"instruction": "Apply your reconciled adjustments to each comparable. Use a NEGATIVE value where the comp is superior to the subject, and a POSITIVE value where it is inferior. Comps 1 and 3 both require GLA adjustments but in opposite directions (Comp 1 larger, Comp 3 smaller).", "applicable": {"C1": ["gla"], "C2": ["bath"], "C3": ["gla"]}, "method_dropdown": ["Paired Sales Analysis", "Grouped Paired Sales", "Cost-Based Support", "Income Differential / GRM", "Regression Analysis", "Appraiser Judgment / Extraction"], "support_min_chars": 15}, "step4": {"show_net_gross_panel": false}}'::jsonb,
  '{"step1_correct_flags": {"C1": ["gla"], "C2": ["bath"], "C3": ["gla"]}, "step1_rationale": "Comp 1 is 150 SF larger than the subject (superior GLA, requires negative adjustment). Comp 2 has 2.5 bathrooms versus the subject''s 2 full (superior, requires negative adjustment). Comp 3 is 120 SF smaller than the subject (inferior GLA, requires positive adjustment). All other features are equivalent across all three comparables.", "step2_tables": {"paired": {"gla": {"pair_answers": [47.0, 47.67, 49.0], "concluded_range": [47.0, 49.0], "rationale": "Three pairs produce $47.00, $47.67, and $49.00/SF — a tight $2 spread that constitutes strong, consistent market support. Reconcile near the midpoint."}, "bath": {"pair_answers": [6200, 6500], "concluded_range": [6200, 6500], "rationale": "Two pairs bracket the half-bath increment at $6,200 and $6,500 — tight market support."}}, "cost": {"gla": {"answer": 48.13, "rationale": "$78.00 × (1 − 0.383) = $48.13/SF. Falls within the paired sales range — convergent evidence from both methods, particularly defensible under cross-examination."}, "bath": {"answer": 6787, "rationale": "$11,000 × (1 − 0.383) = $6,787. Cost exceeds paired sales of $6,200–$6,500 — cost is a ceiling here. Weight paired sales."}}}, "step2_reconciliation": {"gla": {"range": [47.0, 49.0], "rationale": "Paired sales support $47–$49/SF (three tightly clustered pairs). Cost support of $48.13/SF falls within the paired sales range — convergent evidence from both methods. This convergence is particularly valuable in litigation; reconcile near the midpoint at approximately $48/SF."}, "bath": {"range": [6200, 6500], "rationale": "Paired sales bracket $6,200–$6,500. Cost support of $6,787 modestly exceeds paired sales — a credible ceiling. Weight paired sales; reconcile within the paired bracket."}}, "step3_adjustments": {"C1": {"gla": {"direction": "negative", "amount_per_unit": -48.0, "units": 150, "computed_amount": -7200, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 1 is 150 SF larger than the subject (superior). At the reconciled rate of $48/SF, the GLA adjustment is −$7,200."}}, "C2": {"bath": {"direction": "negative", "amount": -6350, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 2 has 2.5 bathrooms versus the subject''s 2 full (superior). The half-bath increment from paired sales is approximately $6,350 (midpoint of $6,200–$6,500)."}}, "C3": {"gla": {"direction": "positive", "amount_per_unit": 48.0, "units": 120, "computed_amount": 5760, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 3 is 120 SF smaller than the subject (inferior). At the reconciled rate of $48/SF, the GLA adjustment is +$5,760."}}}, "step4_adjusted_prices": {"C1": {"unadjusted": 278000, "adjusted": 270800}, "C2": {"unadjusted": 272500, "adjusted": 266150}, "C3": {"unadjusted": 261000, "adjusted": 266760}}, "step4_reconciliation_narrative": "Adjusted prices cluster in a tight band of approximately $266,150–$270,800. There is no contract price in this litigation assignment — the appraiser''s role is to form an independent opinion. The convergence of GLA paired sales and cost support ($47–$49/SF and $48.13/SF respectively) is the most defensible aspect of this analysis under cross-examination. Comp 2 is the most similar comparable before adjustment (single small bath adjustment) and deserves the most weight. The opinion of value is well-centered in the mid-$266,000 to mid-$270,000 range, with adequate support from convergent methodologies.", "tolerance_note": "Student answers are accepted within ±5% of model derived values for paired-sales calculations and within the indicated reconciliation range. Step 3 adjustments accepted within ±13% of the computed amount for GLA and ±12% for bath."}'::jsonb
FROM scenarios s
JOIN scenario_categories sc ON sc.id = s.category_id
JOIN module_sections ms ON ms.id = sc.section_id
JOIN section_fields f ON f.section_id = ms.id AND f.field_key = 'adjustment_grid'
WHERE sc.code = 'M2-S4-C2'
  AND s.order_index = 1;

