rior). Comp 3 receives three upward adjustments (GLA, market conditions, functional — all inferior). For Comp 3 (market conditions): calculate as $368,000 × 10 months × your reconciled %/mo ÷ 100. Each rationale must identify a recognized, peer-accepted methodology and cite specific pairs.", "applicable": {"C1": ["gla", "gar", "loc"], "C2": ["cnd"], "C3": ["gla", "date", "func"]}, "method_dropdown": ["Paired Sales Analysis", "Location Paired Sales Analysis", "Market Conditions (Resale Pairs)", "Cost-Based Support", "Functional Obsolescence (Paired Sales)", "Grouped Paired Sales", "Regression Analysis", "Appraiser Judgment / Extraction"], "support_min_chars": 15}, "step4": {"show_net_gross_panel": true}}'::jsonb,
  '{"step1_correct_flags": {"C1": ["gla", "gar", "loc"], "C2": ["cnd"], "C3": ["gla", "date", "func"]}, "step1_rationale": "Comp 1 differs in three superior features: 150 SF larger (GLA), 3-car garage vs. 2-car (Garage), amenitied/gated location (Location). Comp 2 differs in only one feature: average condition vs. the subject''s good condition (Condition, inferior). Comp 3 differs in three inferior features: 150 SF smaller (GLA), sold 10 months ago (Market Conditions), and non-conforming layout (Functional, incurable). Bedrooms and bathrooms are equivalent across all three comparables.", "step2_tables": {"paired": {"gla": {"pair_answers": [45.33, 46.33, 48.0, 52.8], "concluded_range": [45.0, 48.0], "rationale": "Pairs 1–3 cluster tightly at $45.33–$48.00/SF — strong, consistent market support. Pair 4 produces $52.80/SF and must be excluded under Daubert with documented reasoning (different submarket, anomalous transaction, or data anomaly). Bracket conclusion in the $45–$48/SF range."}, "gar": {"pair_answers": [8500, 8800, 9100], "concluded_range": [8500, 9100], "rationale": "Three pairs produce $8,500, $8,800, and $9,100 — a tight $600 spread. Strong paired sales support for the garage stall increment."}, "loc": {"pair_answers": [15000, 15000, 15500, 16700], "concluded_range": [15000, 15500], "rationale": "Pairs 1–3 produce $15,000–$15,500 — tight market support. Pair 4''s $16,700 is an outlier; address it but do not weight heavily. Reconcile within Pairs 1–3."}, "cnd": {"pair_answers": [11600, 11800, 11700], "concluded_range": [11600, 11800], "rationale": "Three pairs produce $11,600, $11,700, and $11,800 — a $200 spread, the tightest in the analysis."}, "date": {"pair_answers": [0.34, 0.325, 0.304], "concluded_range": [0.31, 0.34], "rationale": "Three resale pairs produce 0.30%, 0.33%, and 0.34%/mo. Tight market support for monthly appreciation rate."}, "func": {"pair_answers": [12000, 11700, 12250], "concluded_range": [11700, 12250], "rationale": "Three pairs produce $11,700–$12,250 — tight market support for the functional obsolescence increment. The non-conforming layout deficiency is documented as incurable in each paired sale."}}, "cost": {"gla": {"answer": 45.6, "rationale": "$76.00 × (1 − 0.40) = $45.60/SF. Falls within the paired sales range of $45.33–$48.00/SF — convergent evidence from both methods. Particularly strong support under Daubert when both independent methodologies agree."}, "gar": {"answer": 13200, "rationale": "$22,000 × (1 − 0.60) = $13,200. Significantly exceeds paired sales of $8,500–$9,100. Cost is a ceiling only — the market does not pay full replacement cost for additional garage stalls. Weight paired sales heavily."}}}, "step2_reconciliation": {"gla": {"range": [45.0, 48.0], "rationale": "Paired sales support $45.33–$48.00/SF (Pairs 1–3). Pair 4 ($52.80/SF) excluded with documented Daubert reasoning. Cost support of $45.60/SF falls within the paired range — rare convergent evidence. Reconcile near $46.50/SF."}, "gar": {"range": [8500, 9100], "rationale": "Three paired sales bracket $8,500–$9,100. Cost of $13,200 exceeds paired sales significantly — market does not pay full replacement for additional stalls. Cost is ceiling only; weight paired sales."}, "loc": {"range": [15000, 15500], "rationale": "Paired sales support $15,000–$15,500 (Pairs 1–3). Pair 4 ($16,700) addressed but not weighted. No cost method applicable. Reconcile within Pairs 1–3 bracket."}, "cnd": {"range": [11600, 11800], "rationale": "Three pairs produce $200 spread — exceptionally tight support. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near $11,700."}, "date": {"range": [0.31, 0.34], "rationale": "Paired sales support 0.31–0.34%/mo. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near 0.325%/mo."}, "func": {"range": [11700, 12250], "rationale": "Paired sales support $11,700–$12,250 for the non-conforming layout deficiency. No cost method applicable for incurable functional obsolescence. Reconcile near $11,975."}}, "step3_adjustments": {"C1": {"gla": {"direction": "negative", "amount_per_unit": -46.5, "units": 150, "computed_amount": -6975, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 1 is 150 SF larger than the subject (superior). At reconciled $46.50/SF (drawn from Pairs 1–3), the GLA adjustment is approximately −$6,975."}, "gar": {"direction": "negative", "amount": -8800, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 1 has a 3-car garage versus the subject''s 2-car (superior). The stall increment from three paired sales is approximately $8,800 (midpoint of $8,500–$9,100)."}, "loc": {"direction": "negative", "amount": -15250, "method": "Location Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 1 is in an amenitied/gated community (superior). The location premium derived from Pairs 1–3 is approximately $15,250."}}, "C2": {"cnd": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 11700, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 2 is in average condition versus the subject''s good condition (inferior). The condition increment from three tightly-clustered pairs is approximately $11,700."}}, "C3": {"gla": {"direction": "positive", "amount_per_unit": 46.5, "units": 150, "computed_amount": 6975, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 3 is 150 SF smaller than the subject (inferior). At reconciled $46.50/SF, the GLA adjustment is approximately +$6,975."}, "date": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 11960, "method": "Market Conditions (Resale Pairs)", "rationale": "Comp 3 sold 10 months ago (inferior date in an appreciating market). At reconciled 0.325%/mo: $368,000 × 10 × 0.325 ÷ 100 = $11,960."}, "func": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 11975, "method": "Functional Obsolescence (Paired Sales)", "rationale": "Comp 3 has a non-conforming layout (incurable functional obsolescence). The deficiency is documented as incurable in three paired sales producing $11,700–$12,250. Reconciled at approximately $11,975."}}}, "step4_adjusted_prices": {"C1": {"unadjusted": 382000, "adjusted": 350975}, "C2": {"unadjusted": 341000, "adjusted": 352700}, "C3": {"unadjusted": 368000, "adjusted": 398910}}, "step4_reconciliation_narrative": "The adjusted prices reveal the central teaching point of this scenario. Comps 1 and 2 cluster tightly at approximately $351,000 and $352,700 — strong, mutually-supporting evidence. Comp 3''s adjusted price of approximately $398,900 is well above the cluster, reflecting its three simultaneous upward adjustments totaling approximately $30,910 (gross adjustment of approximately 8.4%). Under Daubert, this gross adjustment magnitude requires explicit weighting commentary: Comp 3 is included as a market data point but given REDUCED WEIGHT in the final value opinion. The advanced-level teaching points are: (1) the GLA Pair 4 outlier must be excluded with documented Daubert reasoning, (2) four of six adjustment types lack cost support and rely entirely on paired sales evidence, (3) functional obsolescence requires the most rigorous rationale of any adjustment type — confirming the deficiency is incurable and citing specific paired sales evidence, and (4) Comp 3''s gross adjustment burden requires explicit weighting commentary rather than simple inclusion. The final opinion of value, drawing primary weight from Comps 1 and 2, supports a value of approximately $350,000–$355,000 for partition purposes. This conclusion is supported by Daubert-compliant methodologies for all six adjustment types.", "tolerance_note": "Student answers are accepted within ±5% of model derived values for paired-sales calculations and within the indicated reconciliation range. Step 3 adjustments accepted within ±13% of the computed amount for GLA, ±12% for garage, location, condition, and functional, and ±16% for market conditions."}'::jsonb
FROM scenarios s
JOIN scenario_categories sc ON sc.id = s.category_id
JOIN module_sections ms ON ms.id = sc.section_id
JOIN section_fields f ON f.section_id = ms.id AND f.field_key = 'adjustment_grid'
WHERE sc.code = 'M2-S4-C2'
  AND s.order_index = 3;

COMMIT;

